UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1735
1 (1) The definition and characteristics of dyslexia;
2 (2) Processes for identifying dyslexia;
3 (3) Evidence-based interventions and accommodations for dyslexia and other disorders
4 defined in KRS 158.305 and related literacy and learning challenges; and
5 (4) Core elements of a response-to-intervention framework addressing reading, writing,
6 mathematics, and behavior, including;
7 (a) Universal screening;
8 (b) Evidence-based research interventions;
9 (c) Progress monitoring of the effectiveness of interventions on student
10 performance;
11 (d) Data-based decision-making procedures related to:
12 1. Determining intervention effectiveness on student performance; and
13 2. Determining the need to continue, alter, or discontinue interventions or
14 conduct further evaluation of student needs; and
15 (e) Application and implementation of a multitiered system of
16 supports[response-to-intervention] and dyslexia instructional practices in the
17 classroom setting.
